nihongo Lexus   is the luxury vehicle division of Japanese automaker Toyota Toyota Motor Corporation. First introduced in 1989 in the United States,cite web  url=http://pressroom.toyota.com/fact-sheets/history+of+lexus+brochure+2011.htm  title=The History of Lexus 2011 Brochure  accessdate=2011-07-07  publisher=Toyota USA newsroom  year=2011 Lexus is now sold globally and has become Japan's largest-selling make of premium cars. The Lexus marque is marketed in over 70 countries and territories worldwide,cite web url=http://www.roadandtrack.com/tests/drives/2010_lexus_rx_350_rx_450h title=2010 Lexus RX 350 & RX 450h - First Drive work=Road & Track accessdate=2010-05-15 last=Wilson first=Tom date=2009-02-13 and has ranked among the ten largest Japanese global brands in market value.cite web url=http://www.interbrand.com/Libraries/Files/-1_Japan_BGB2009_pdf.sflb.ashx title=Japan's Best Global Brands 2009 year=2009 work=Interbrand accessdate=2010-09-20 Lexus is headquartered in Nagoya, Japan. Operational centers are located in Brussels, Belgium, and Torrance, California, United States.

Lexus originated from a clandestine flagship car flagship sedan project, code-named F1, which began in 1983 and culminated in the launch of the original Lexus LS in 1989. Subsequently, the division added sedan car sedan, coup, convertible, and Sport utility vehicle SUV models. In 2005, a hybrid vehicle hybrid version of the Lexus RX RX crossover debuted, and additional hybrid models later joined the division's lineup. In 2007, Lexus launched its own Lexus#F marque F marque performance division with the debut of the Lexus IS F IS F sport sedan, followed by the Lexus LFA LFA supercar in 2009.

From the start of production, Lexus vehicles have been produced in Japan, with manufacturing centered in the Chbu region Chbu and Kysh regions, and in particular at Toyota's Tahara plant Tahara, Aichi Prefecture Aichi, Chbu and Miyata, Fukuoka Miyata, Fukuoka Prefecture Fukuoka, Kysh plants. Assembly of the first Lexus built outside the country, the Ontario, Canada-produced RX 330, began in 2003. Following a corporate reorganization from 2001 to 2005, Lexus also operates its own automotive design design, automotive engineering engineering, and manufacturing centers, solely responsible for the division's vehicles.

Since the 2000s, Lexus has increased sales outside its largest market in the United States through an ongoing global expansion. The division inaugurated Car dealership dealerships in Japan's Japanese domestic market domestic market in 2005, becoming the first Japanese premium car marque to launch in its country of origin. Further debuts in Southeast Asia, Latin America, Europe, and other  export regions have since followed. The division's lineup has also been expanded to reflect regional specifications in model and powertrain configurations.
TOC limit 3

 History 

 1980s: The F1 project 
In 1983, Toyota chairman Eiji Toyoda summoned a secret meeting of company executives, to whom he posed the question, Can we create a luxury vehicle to challenge the world's best?Harvnb May 2006 p=43 This question prompted Toyota to embark on a top-secret project, code-named F1 Flagship One.Harvnb May 2006 p=42 The F1 project, whose finished product was ultimately the Lexus LS Lexus LS 400, aimed to develop a flagship sedan that would expand Toyotas product line, giving it a foothold in the premium segment and offering both longtime and new customers an upmarket product.cite web url=http://www.autolinedetroit.tv/autoline/watch.php?stream=927 title=How Lexus Was Successful in the U.S. interview year=2006 format=WMV last=Press first=Jim accessdate=2006 publisher=Auto Line Detroit The F1 project followed the success of the Toyota Supra sports car and the premium Toyota Cressida models.White, John. New Route for Japanese Cars: Luxury. The Boston Globe. 1989-10-23 Both the Supra and Cressida were rear-wheel drive cars with a powerful Toyota 7M-GE 7M-GE/7M-GTE inline-six engine. The largest sedan Toyota built at the time was the limited-production, 1960s-vintage Toyota Century, its domestic, hand built, limousine flagship and sole V8-powered model, followed by the inline-six-engined Toyota Crown premium sedan.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=67, 63Harvnb Long 2001 pp=1621 The Century was conservatively styled for the Japanese market, and along with the Crown not slated for export. F1 designers targeted their new sedan at international markets and began development on a new V8 engine.

The opportunity for Japanese manufacturers to export more expensive models had grown in the 1980s due to Voluntary Export Restraints voluntary export restraints, negotiated by the Japanese government and U.S. trade representatives, restricting mainstream car sales.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=xix, 28 In 1986, Honda launched its Acura marque in the U.S., influencing Toyota's plans for a luxury division;Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=109 the initial Acura model was an export version of the Honda Legend, itself launched in Japan in 1985 as a rival to the Toyota Crown, Nissan Cedric/Nissan Gloria Gloria and Mazda Luce.cite web url= http://www.zakzak.co.jp/society/domestic/news/20100716/dms1007161623011-n2.htm title=Honda's premium sedan, Legend language=Japanese work=Sankei Shimbun date=2010-07-16 accessdate=2011-01-31 In 1987, Nissan Motor Co., Ltd. Nissan unveiled its plans for a premium brand, Infiniti,Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=72, 88, 116 and revised its flagship Nissan President sedan in standard wheelbase form for export as the Infiniti Q45, which it launched in 1990.cite web url=http://gazoo.com/meishakan/meisha/shousai.asp?R_ID=5498&ex_spec=shousai title=Profile: 1990 Nissan President language=Japanese publisher=Gazoo accessdate=2011-01-31 year=2011 In 1988, Mazda began selling the Luce as the Mazda 929 in North America, and later began plans to develop an upscale marque, to be called Mazda#Marques Amati, but its plans did not come to fruition.

Toyota researchers visited the U.S. in May 1985 to conduct focus groups and market research on luxury consumers.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=35, 41 During that time, several F1 designers rented a home in Laguna Beach, California to observe the lifestyles and tastes of American upper class consumers. Meanwhile, F1 engineering teams conducted prototype testing on locations ranging from the German autobahn to U.S. roads.cite web url=http://www.edmunds.com/lexus/ title=Edmunds.com Lexus Overview publisher=Edmunds.com accessdate=2011-05-23 Toyotas market research concluded that a separate brand name brand and sales channel were needed to present its new flagship sedan, and plans were made to develop a new network of dealerships in the U.S. market.Harvnb Morgan Liker 2006 p=121

= Brand development =
File:Lexus Balance ad.jpg thumb Lexus made its Balance advertisement television debut with champagne glasses stacked on the hood of a revving LS 400. alt=Car front view, halfway lit, with 15 champagne glasses stacked on the hood to form a triangle.
In 1986, Toyotas longtime advertising agency Saatchi & Saatchi formed a specialized unit, Team One, to handle marketing for the new premium brand. Image consulting firm Lippincott Mercer Lippincott & Margulies was hired to develop a list of 219 prospective names; Vectre, Verone, Chaparel, Calibre and Alexis were chosen as top candidates.Harvnb Mahler 2004 pp=5657 While Alexis quickly became the front runner, concerns were raised that the name applied to people more than cars being associated with the Alexis Carrington character on the popular 1980s primetime drama Dynasty TV series Dynasty, and as a result the first letter was removed and the i replaced with a u to morph the name to Lexus.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=111

The etymology of the Lexus name has been attributed to the combination of the words luxury and elegance,cite news url=http://www.forbes.com/facesinthenews/2005/07/26/toyota-lexus-autos-cx_cn_0726autofacescan02.html title=Watanabe's Toyota Rolls Out Lexus In Japan date=2005-07-26 work=Forbes last=Noon first=Chris accessdate=2008-06-05 and another theory claims it is an acronym for luxury exports to the U.S. According to Team One interviews, the brand name has no specific meaning and simply denotes a luxurious and technological image. Just prior to the release of the first vehicles, database service LexisNexis obtained a temporary injunction forbidding the name Lexus from being used as they stated it might cause confusion.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=12830 The injunction threatened to delay the division's launch and marketing efforts. Upon reflection, a U.S. appeals court lifted the injunction, deciding that there was little likelihood of confusion between the two products.

The original Lexus slogan, developed after Team One representatives visited Lexus designers in Japan and noted an obsessive attention to detail, became The Relentless Pursuit of Perfection.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=11314 The Lexus logo was developed by Molly Designs and Hunter Communications.cite web url=http://www.mollydesigns.com/history.html title=Molly Designs history, Lexus logo design publisher=Molly Designs archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080611081501/http://www.mollydesigns.com/history.html archivedate=2008-06-11cite web url=http://huntercommunications.com/HCmain/company/lexus.html title=An Enduring Symbol of Excellence publisher=Hunter Communications archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/2003040715380/http://huntercommunications.com/HCmain/company/lexus.html archivedate=2003-04-07 The final design for the Lexus logo featured a stylized L within an oval, and according to Toyota, was rendered using a precise mathematical formula. The first teaser ads featuring the Lexus name and logo, designed by Team One, appeared at the Chicago, Los Angeles, and New York auto shows in 1988.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=115

= Launch =
File:Lexus LS 400 UCF10 I.jpg thumb The Lexus LS#XF10 LS 400 flagship sedan launched in 1989, introducing Lexus to the world. alt=Front quarter view of a sedan parked on a street.

In 1989, after an extended development process involving 60 designers, 24 engineering teams, 1,400 engineers, 2,300 technicians, 220 support workers, around 450 prototypes, and over USD 1 billion in costs, the F1 project was completed.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=24 The resulting flagship, the Lexus LS 400, had a unique design that shared no major elements with previous Toyota vehicles, with a new 4.0 L V8 engine V8 Four-stroke cycle gasoline engine and rear-wheel drive.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=xxi, 69Harvnb Mahler 2004 p=31 The LS 400 debuted in January 1989 at the North American International Auto Show in Detroit, and officially went on sale the following September at a network of 81 new Lexus dealerships across the U.S.Harvnb May 2006 p=47 The LS 400 was sold along with a smaller sibling, the Toyota Vista#V20 Toyota Camry-based Lexus ES ES 250. The launch of Lexus was heralded by a multimillion dollar advertising campaign in both television and print media.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=11718

At its debut, the LS 400 was widely praised for its quietness, well-appointed and ergonomic interior, engine performance, build Quality business quality, aerodynamics, Fuel economy in automobiles fuel economy, and value,Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=6876 although it was criticized by some automobile columnists for derivative styling and a suspension vehicle suspension regarded as too compromising of handling for ride comfort.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=726 The LS 400 debuted at USD 38,000 in the U.S. in some markets, it was priced against mid-size six-cylinder Mercedes-Benz and BMW modelscite web url=http://www.edmunds.com/insideline/do/Features/articleId=115368  title=Lexus LS 400, LS 430 and LS 460 Generations:  Setting the Standard in the Most Comfortable Way Possible accessdate=2010-07-08 publisher=Edmunds.com date=2003-03-13  archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080705230718/http://www.edmunds.com/insideline/do/Features/articleId=115368  archivedate = 2008-07-05 and was rated by Car and Driver magazine as better than both the USD 63,000 Mercedes-Benz Mercedes-Benz W126 420 SEL and the USD 55,000 BMW BMW E32 735i in terms of ride, handling, and performance.cite news url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,971153-1,00.html title=New Kid on The Dock date=1990-09-17 accessdate=2007-04-29 last=Detroit first=S.C. Gwynne work=Time Magazine The LS 400 also won major Lexus LS awards list motoring awards from publications including Automobile Magazine and Wheels Magazine.Davis, David E. 1990 All-Stars, Automobile Magazine. 1990-01.cite web url=http://www.wheelsmag.com.au/wheels/site/articleIDs/C40CA2CB6C8577F1CA257285001E7302?open&template=domWheels title=Wheels' COTY the real McCoy last=Gable first=Chris work=Wheels Magazine 2006-12-04 accessdate=2007-05-15 Despite being an upstart, Lexus established instant customer loyalty and its debut was generally regarded as a major shock to the pedigree luxury marques. BMW's and Mercedes-Benz's U.S. sales figures dropped 29% and 19%, respectively, with BMW executives accusing Lexus of Dumping pricing policy dumping in that market, while 35% of Lexus buyers traded in a Lincoln or Cadillac to make their purchase.
File:Lexus SC 400 1991.jpg thumb left In 1991, the Lexus SC#Z30 SC 400 coupe became the third Lexus model to debut. alt=Front quarter view of a coupe.

In December 1989, Lexus initiated a voluntary recall of all 8,000 LS 400s sold to date, based upon two customer complaints over defective wiring and an overheated brake light. In a sweeping 20-day operation which replaced the parts on all affected vehicles, Lexus sent technicians to pick up, repair, and return cars to customers free of charge, and also flew in personnel and rented garage space for owners in remote locations. This response was lauded in media publications and helped establish the marque's early reputation for customer service.cite web url=http://www.autonews.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20060327/SUB/60322012/1003 title=How a recall earned Lexus a top reputation  work=Automotive News accessdate=2009-02-19 last=Denove first=Chris date=2006-03-27 coauthors=Power, JamesHarvnb Long 2001 pp=3839

By 1989's end, 16,392 LS 400 and ES 250 sedans had been sold in the four months following the U.S. launch.Harvnb Long 2001 p=36 Although sales had begun at a slower pace than expected, the final tally matched the division's target of 16,000 units for that year.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=125, 141 Following initial models, plans called for the addition of a sports coupe along with a redesigned ES sedan.
clear

1990s: Growth and expansion
Image:Lexus-ES300.jpg thumb  The Lexus ES#XV10 ES 300 sedan arrived in 1991 and was the best-selling Lexus for most of the 1990s. alt=Front quarter view of an sedan.
In 1990, during its first full year of sales, Lexus sold 63,594 LS 400 and ES 250 sedans in the U.S.,Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=13941 the vast majority being the LS model. That year, Lexus also began limited exports to the United Kingdom, Switzerland, Canada, and Australia.Harvnb Long 2001 pp=4142 In 1991, Lexus launched its first sports coupe, the Lexus SC SC 400, which shared the LS 400s V8 engine and rear-wheel drive design. This was followed by the second generation Lexus ES#Second generation VCV10 ES 300 sedan, which succeeded the ES 250 and became Lexus' top seller.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=14146 At the conclusion of 1991, Lexus had become the top-selling premium car import in the U.S.,cite web url=http://autos.msn.com/browse/Lexus.aspx title=Overview: The Lexus Story year=2008 publisher=MSN Autos accessdate=2008-12-25Harvnb Long 2001 p=51 with sales reaching a total of 71,206 vehicles. That year, Lexus ranked highest in J.D. Power and Associates' studies on initial vehicle quality, customer satisfaction, and sales satisfaction for the first time.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=75 The marque also began increasing U.S. model prices past those of comparable American premium makes, but still below high-end European models; by 1992, the LS 400's base price had risen 18% to nearly USD 45,000.Harvnb Long 2001 p=57

In 1993, Lexus launched the mid-size Lexus GS GS 300 sports sedan, based on the Toyota Aristo using the List of Toyota platforms#S Toyota S platform from the Toyota Crown, which had sold for two years prior in Japan. The GS 300 was priced below the LS 400 in the marque's lineup.Harvnb Long 2001 p=73 That same year, Lexus also became one of the first marques to debut a certified pre-owned program, with the aim of improving trade-in model values.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=149 In 1994, the marque introduced the second generation LS 400, a complete redesign of its flagship model.Harvnb Long 2001 p=89 In May 1995, sales were threatened by the U.S. government's proposal of 100% tariffs on upscale Japanese cars in response to the widening U.S.-Japan trade deficit.cite web url=http://www.autonews.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20071029/ANA03/710290340/1128/ANA03&Profile=1128 title=Bold moves halt tariff stalemate, save Lexus brand work=Automotive News accessdate=2009-02-02 date=2007-10-29 last=Treece first=James SUVs were exempt from the proposed sanctions.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=16061 Normal sales operations resumed by late 1995 when the Japanese auto manufacturers collectively agreed to greater American investments, and the tariffs were not enacted.

Image:Lexus-RX300 side.JPG thumb left The first Lexus RX#XU10 RX 300 crossover SUV debuted in 1998. alt=Front quarter view of an SUV.
In 1996, Lexus debuted its first sport utility vehicle, the Lexus LX LX 450,Harvnb Long 2001 pp=10507 followed by the third generation ES 300 sedan. The marque's plans for developing an SUV model had accelerated during the U.S.-Japan tariff discussions of 1995. In 1998, Lexus added the first luxury-branded crossover SUV, the Lexus RX RX 300, and the second generation GS 300 and GS 400 sedans. The RX crossover targeted suburban buyers who desired an upmarket SUV but did not need the LX's off-road capability; it was particularly successful, becoming the marque's top-selling model ahead of the ES 300.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=17172 The same year, Lexus made its debut in South America's most populous country when it launched sales in Brazil.cite web url=http://www.estadao.com.br/suplementos/not_sup342035,0.htm title=Em busca de notoriedade work=Estadao language=Portuguese accessdate=2009-06-08 date=2009-03-20cite web url=http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/2000/03/19/050002.htm title=Tecnologia  destaque no Lexus ES 300  work=Dirio do Nordeste accessdate=2009-06-08 language=Portuguese date=2000-03-19 In 1999, Lexus recorded its one-millionth vehicle sold in the U.S. market, and was ranked as the top-selling premium car maker in the U.S. overall.
clear

 2000s: Global reorganization 
Image:Lexus-RX400h Crystal White Mica.jpg thumb right The Lexus RX XU30 RX 400h, the first hybrid version of Lexus' best-selling vehicle, debuted in 2004. alt=Front quarter view of an SUV parked next to a beach.
In 2000, Lexus introduced the Lexus IS IS line, a new series of entry-level sport sedans.  In 2001, the marque debuted its first convertible, the SC 430, a redesigned ES 300, and the third generation LS 430.Mahler 204, pp. 27, 196. The GX 470 mid-size SUV debuted in 2002, followed by the second generation RX 330 in 2003.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=189 The following year, Lexus recorded its two-millionth U.S. vehicle sale,cite web url=http://wardsdealer.com/ar/auto_millionth_lexus_customer/ title=2-Millionth Lexus Customer quote=RX 330 owner Steven Sandman, trip winner date=2004-06-01 work=Ward's DealerHarvnb Dawson 2004 p=xxiv and debuted the first luxury-branded production hybrid SUV, the Lexus RX XU30 RX 400h.cite news url=http://www.dailynews.com/search/ci_3076458 title=Lexus introduces first luxury hybrid SUV date=2005-10-26 agency=Associated Press last=Job first=Ann accessdate=2008-06-21 This vehicle used a Hybrid Synergy Drive Lexus Hybrid Drive system which combined gasoline and electric motors for increased power, fuel efficiency, and lower emissions relative to gasoline-only equivalents.cite web url=http://www.businessweek.com/autos/content/mar2006/bw20060308_999129.htm   title=Hybrid Heaven in a Lexus last=Petersen first=Thane work=BusinessWeek date=2006-03-08 accessdate=2007-05-06

In 2005, Lexus completed an organizational separation from parent company Toyota,cite web url=http://www.autofieldguide.com/articles/090601.html title=Lexus Comes Into Its Own publisher=Automotive Design & Production last=Vasilash first=Gary year=2006 accessdate=2007-05-06 with dedicated design, engineering, training, and manufacturing centers working exclusively for the division.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=199200cite news url=http://www.findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m3012/is_11_183/ai_110404995 publisher=Automotive Industries title=The pursuit of higher sales: new Lexus managing officer date=2003-11 accessdate=2007-05-06 This effort coincided with Lexus' launch in its home market of Japan and an expanded global launch of the brand in major world markets such as China.cite web url=http://auto.qq.com/a/20050303/000011.htm  title=Lexus luxury to expand market in China date=2005-03-03 work=Xinmin News accessdate=2010-09-20 language=Mandarin  archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20050308234010/http://auto.qq.com/a/20050303/000011.htm  archivedate = 2005-03-08 Executives aimed to increase Lexus sales outside of its largest market in the U.S.cite web url=http://www.nni.nikkei.co.jp/AC/TNKS/Nni20080226D26JFF01.htm
 title=Lexus to increase production capacity by 35% date=2008-02-26 publisher=Nikkei Business Daily accessdate=2008-02-27 To accompany this expansion, next generation Lexus vehicles were redesigned as global models for international release.Harvnb Dawson 2004 p=210 In the European market, where Lexus had long faced struggling sales owing to low brand recognition, few dedicated dealerships, and 1990s import quotas,Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=194195Lexus Magic Fails to Capture Europeans. Detroit News. 2005-11-23. Retrieved on 2006. the marque announced plans to introduce hybrid and diesel powertrains,cite news url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/4309743.stm title=Toyota targets Europe's urban youth date=2005-03-01 publisher=BBC News last=Madslien   first=Jorn  accessdate=2008-06-21 increase the number of Lexus dealerships, and expand operations in emerging markets such as Russia.cite web url=http://b-ru.com/economics/general/170-sales-results-foreign-cars-russia-2007/ archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20110707202658/http://b-ru.com/economics/general/170-sales-results-foreign-cars-russia-2007/ archivedate=2011-07-07 title=Sales' results of foreign cars in Russia in 2007  date=2008-01-15 publisher=InvestExp last=Association of European Business in Russian Federation accessdate=2008-09-30cite web url=http://blogs.motortrend.com/lexus-is-f-plus-jim-chris-farley-1114.html
 title=Lexus IS F, Plus Jim & Chris Farley date=2007-09-27 work=Motor Trend last=St. Antoine   first=Arthur accessdate=2011-07-29

File:Lexus IS250 silver.jpg thumb left The second generation Lexus IS line debuted in 2005, and an F marque variant arrived in 2007. alt=Front quarter view of a sedan.

Lexus' arrival in the Japanese market in July 2005 marked the first introduction of a Japanese premium car marque in the domestic market.Toyota Opens Lexus Dealerships in Japan. CBS News. 2005-08-30. Retrieved on 2008-06-21. New generation LS, IS, ES, GS and RX models subsequently became available in Japan along with the SC 430, ending domestic sales of Toyota-branded models under the Celsior, Altezza, Windom, Aristo, Harrier and Soarer nameplates, respectively. The Altezza and Aristo were previously exclusive to Japanese Toyota retail sales channels called Toyota#Japan Toyota Vista Store, the Windom was exclusive to Toyota Corolla Store, the Celsior and Harrier were exclusive to Toyopet Store, and the Soarer was previously available at both Toyota Store and Toyopet Store locations.Harvnb Dawson 2004 pp=19293 Lexus models sold in Japan featured higher specifications and a price premium from 1-million and up compared with their discontinued Toyota counterparts. Sales for the first half-year were slower than expected,cite web url=http://www.businessweek.com/autos/content/feb2006/bw20060215_597701.htm title=Lexus Sales Sputter at Home work=BusinessWeek last=Rowley first=Ian date=2006-02-15 accessdate=2007-05-06
affected by the contraction of the domestic auto market and price increases, but improved in subsequent months with an expanded lineup.cite web url=http://wardsdealer.com/latest/lexus_progressing_japan/ title=Lexus Slowly Progressing in Japan last=Schreffler first=Roger coauthors=Chrysler, Mack date=2007-12-28 accessdate=2007-04-18 publisher=Ward's Dealer Businesscite web url=http://www.greencarcongress.com/2009/08/hs250h-triple-20090808.html title=Toyota to Nearly Triple Production of Lexus HS 250h Hybrid by October work=Green Car Congress accessdate=2009-09-25 date=2009-08-08

Through the mid-2000s, Lexus experienced sales successes in South Korea and Taiwan, becoming the top-selling import make in both markets in 2005;Toyota's Lexus Remains Best-Selling Foreign Car in Korea. The Korea Times. 2007-01-05. Retrieved on 2007-01-07.cite web url=http://cens.com/cens/html/en/news/news_inner_3938.html title=Lexus #1 Luxury Import in Taiwan date=2006-01-19 publisher=Taiwan Economic News accessdate=2007-05-06 the marque also sold well in the Middle East, where it ranked first or second among rivals in multiple countries, and in Australia, where Lexus reached third in luxury car sales in 2006.cite web url=http://www.drive.com.au/Editorial/ArticleDetail.aspx?ArticleID=57554 title=Convertible Lexus to take on the Germans work=Sydney Morning Herald#Overview Drive accessdate=2009-05-20 last=Blackburn first=Richard 
Australia Vehicle Sales - 2006 YTD. Driving Australia. 2006-12. Retrieved on 2007-05-06. Division executives in 2006 announced an expansion goal from 68 countries to 76 worldwide by 2010.cite news url=http://jp.reuters.com/article/topNews/idJPJAPAN-27671120070831 title=Lexus targets expansion to 76 countries by 2010 publisher=Reuters language=Japanese date=2007-08-31 accessdate=2009-02-02 date=2007-12-26 By the end of the decade, this expansion resulted in official launches in Malaysia and South Africa in 2006,cite news url=http://news-business.vlex.com/vid/lexus-launched-in-malaysia-77734791 title=Lexus launched in Malaysia date=2007-01-01 publisher=Malaysian Business last=Razif first=Muhd
 accessdate=2012-04-03cite web url=http://www.bizcommunity.com/Article/196/140/18890.html title=Clever marketing boosts Lexus sales publisher=BizCommunity.com accessdate=2009-02-20 date=2007-10-16 Indonesia in 2007,Toyota Indonesia plans to introduce Lexus vehicles. Reuters. 2007-02-21. Retrieved on 2008-06-21. Chile in 2008,cite web url=http://diario.elmercurio.cl/detalle/index.asp?id=008baab8-a618-44cd-a5ff-0ecdef6f3502 title=Lexus en Chile ya es oficial  work=El Mercurio accessdate=2009-05-04 date=2008-03-29 first=Alejandro last=Manrquez language=Portuguesecite web url=http://www.latercera.com/contenido/665_120257_9.shtml title=Lexus: Ao uno en Chile work=La Tercera accessdate=2009-05-04 date=2009-04-18 language=Portuguese and the Philippines in 2009.Mendoza, Al 2009-01-22. Lexus unleashed in historic glory. Business Mirror. Retrieved on 2009-02-02.
