=Hybrids and F models=
File:Lexus GS 450h front.JPG thumb The first Lexus GS S190 GS 450h rear-wheel drive hybrid debuted in 2006. alt=Front quarter view of a sedan.

In 2006, Lexus began sales of the GS 450h, a V6 engine V6 hybrid performance sedan,cite web url=http://www.businessweek.com/autos/content/sep2006/bw20060912_991505.htm?chan=search
 title=2007 Lexus GS 450h date=2006-09-13 work=BusinessWeek last=Peterson first=Thane accessdate=2008-06-21 and launched the fourth generation flagship Lexus LS#Fourth generation USF40/USF41 LS line, comprising both standard- and long-wheelbase V8 LS 460 and LS 460 L and hybrid LS 600h and LS 600h L versions.cite news url=http://www.thestar.com/comment/columnists/article/126053
 title=Quiet crown contender date=2006-09-17 work=The Star Malaysia last=Tojiagic first=Mark accessdate=2008-06-21 location=Toronto The fifth generation ES 350 also debuted in the same year. The LS 600h L subsequently went on sale as the most expensive sedan ever produced in Japan, with a sticker price of approximately USD 125,000.cite web url=http://www.nextautos.com/countriesmarkets/japan/lexus-ls600hl-to-displace-toyota-century-as-japans-priciest-auto
 title=Japan Report: Lexus LS600hl To Displace Toyota Century As Japans Priciest Auto date=2007-05-08 work=Winding Road accessdate=2007-10-01 archivedate=2009-05-10 archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20090510122900/http://www.nextautos.com/countriesmarkets/japan/lexus-ls600hl-to-displace-toyota-century-as-japans-priciest-auto By the end of 2006, Lexus' annual sales had reached 475,000 vehicles worldwide. In January 2007, Lexus announced a new Lexus#F marque F marque performance division, which would produce racing-inspired versions of its performance models. The first of this line, the IS F, made its debut at the 2007 North American International Auto Show,cite web url=http://www.thecarconnection.com/autoshownews/1010188_lexus-confirms-f-performance-cars title=Lexus Confirms F Performance Cars date=2006-12-11 publisher=The Car Connection last=Padgett first=Marty accessdate=2007-05-06 accompanied by a supercar concept, the Lexus LF LF-A.

In October 2007, Lexus entered the SEMA Specialty Equipment Market Association show in the U.S. for the first time with the IS F, and announced its Lexus F#F Sport F-Sport performance trim level and factory-sanctioned accessory line.cite web url=http://www.autoblog.com/2007/10/31/sema-2007-lexus-f-sport-performance-accessories/
